OL,3,CWorkers at steel giant Tata to strike
OL,4,Cin protest against job losses
OL,6,FTata is switching to a greener form of
OL,7,Fsteel production which requires fewer
OL,8,Fstaff, so up to 2,800 jobs are being
OL,9,Fcut.
OL,11,FUnite said it will be the first time
OL,12,Fin over 40 years that steel workers in
OL,13,Fthe UK have taken strike action.
OL,15,FUnite general secretary Sharon Graham
OL,16,Fsaid: "Tata's workers are not just
OL,17,Ffighting for their jobs ` they are
OL,18,Ffighting for the future of their
OL,19,Fcommunities and the future of steel in
OL,20,FWales.
