OL,3,CWorkers at steel giant Tata to strike
OL,4,Cin protest against job losses
OL,6,FThe unions expect an incoming Labour
OL,7,Fgovernment to hold emergency talks
OL,8,Fwith Tata to discuss alternatives to
OL,9,Fits proposals.
OL,11,FTata has made it clear it is pressing
OL,12,Fahead with switching from blast
OL,13,Ffurnace production to an electric arc,
OL,14,Fas other steel companies are doing.
OL,16,FTata says it is losing #1 million a
OL,17,Fday at Port Talbot which it has warned
OL,18,Fis unsustainable.
